metadata.description:
{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This installation will include 4 actions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Update Region Items\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action will copy the items and automation of all child tracks underneath and within the bounds of the selected region items. It will then paste those contents to the child tracks of all paired region items, removing their previous contents. Paired region items are determined by either MIDI pool or item name, depending on the value of the "selectRegionsByName" bool in the settings file.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Update Parent Region Items of Selected Items\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action will navigate through all of the parent tracks of the selected items (including source tracks of receives) and update any parent region items they are contained within.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Update Selected Region Items and Parent Region Items of Selected Items\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action is identical to "Update Parent Region Items of Selected Items", except it will first update any region items you have selected.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clear Selected Region Items\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action clears the contained contents of the child tracks of the selected region items. Used to clean up the contents of a region item if you want to change, move, or remove it.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action will render the tracks you have selected up through all folders they are children of. It will also include sends contained in those folders in the render. You have to set up your render settings to be 'Stems (selected tracks)' for it to work properly though. Also have your render settings have the filename output as the $track wildcard.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script will activate a zoom tool similar to what is used in Melodyne. Be sure to install the default settings file into:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 "Scripts\\Alkamist Scripts\\Zoom Tool\\Zoom Tool Default Settings.lua"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can copy that file into the same folder and call it "Zool Tool User Settings.lua" and change the settings in there. That way, your settings are not overwritten when updating.\par}
}
